            <p class="article-content">    Use block Parmesan cheese and grate it freshly yourself. This will ensure that the cheese melts better. Don’t use dry grated Parmesan cheese because it will not melt. (Some grocery stores do have freshly grated Parmesan off the block in the deli section.)
                Much like cauliflower pizza crust, make sure to squeeze all liquid out of the steamed, ground cauliflower.
                To make cauliflower crisps the same size, I used a cookie scoop to measure the “dough.” I used #40 cookies scoop but you can choose to use a different one.
                Once cauliflower crisps are baked, let them cool before taking them off or they might break.
                When making the crisps, pat the “dough” down and fix the edges as you flatten it. The edges will crack as it spreads but they are easily fixed.</p>
